		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Nope, the PC wins this round. Poorly programmed modern games make the PC the glitchiest system ever. NES games were tiny and simple compared to what we have today on modern systems. Over the years developers have gotten lazy with badly written engines (Crysis) and their 'we've got the money so who cares if its bugged' (Assassin's Creed). All because PCs are so powerful nowadays they can slack off.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


