	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />One inefficiency I've read about is that some engines overtessellate what doesn't need to be tessellated. Another is using primitives other than triangle/quad strips; I've read that GPUs aren't so efficient at handling fans and isolated triangles. Yet another is overly complex shaders.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


